		"description": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">At 10th level as an action, you let out a supernaturally loud roar infused with dragonfear.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">You can force all creatures of your choice within 60 feet to make a Charisma saving throw against your warlock spell save DC.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>On a failure they are frightened of you for 1 minute. Frightened creatures may repeat the save at the end of each of their turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">This counts as a dragon's fear ability for the Draconic Curse ability.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">Once you have used this ability, you cannot do so again until you finish a short or long rest.</p>",
